<br>
When such a relationship has been established the member is invited into the guild and undertakes the path of training /questing to become a fully accepted member, of rank 3 in any house.<br>
<br>
Any full member of at least rank 3, can have any number of sponsored newcomers, but if any of those betray the guild or the sponsor is found to not properly aid them into becoming a part of the guild, these rights of the named sponsor can be altered as seen fit by the highest ranking member of the house or the Lord / Lady of Recruiting.<br>
<br>
To achieve rank 2, the new member have to complete at least 2 quests, as given to him/her by the sponsor. The exact procedure of doing so is : the sponsor gets a feeling of what the member would like to do, and creates a quest accordingly. Such a quest can take almost any form, from writing a guild guide post here to getting a flowing black robe and so forth. The quest is posted in the Members Count Forum under the new members topic. The new member must then reply to this post on whether he/she agrees to undertake this quest or not.. At this point the Lord / Lady of Recruiting has the right / responsibility to check on the quest and change it as seen to be just, so that it both matches the skills and the interests of the new member.<br>
<br>
At this stage the quests are most often some that can be done alone or with few other people, and it often deals with acquiring items for the sponsor; later on quests will become harder, require more guild cooperation, and focus more on the guild treasury growth.<br>
<br>
Upon having completed the given quests and having the completion witnessed and approved by a higher ranking member of the house OR the Lord / Lady of Recruiting as well as the sponsor, the member is awarded rank 2 in the proper house, still serving the same sponsor.<br>
<br>
To achieve rank 3, a member must undertake and complete at least 3 quests, given as prescribed above. On this stage though the quests should focus around acquiring a proper set of items for the new member, for the initiation ceremony, as well as the possibility of requiring more guild cooperation to complete it. All members are expected to help a new member with these quests if it of their appropriate level and they have the time and chance to do so !<br>
<br>
Upon once again completing the required steps and having them accepted by the Lord / Lady of Recruiting, the member is entered for a Membership Ceremony, where a feast shall be held to celebrate the new members completion of initiations, wherein the sponsor will hold a small personal speech and welcome the member to our midst. The sponsor will also grant the new member a gift of proper value and usability by the new member.<br>
<br>
How to achieve ranks higher than 3 are described elsewhere in the Book of Retribution.<br>
<br>
NOTE: Rules are being revised to take into account people we really want to join (ie. officers pest them to join), as well as spouses of current fully acccepted members. For now Carnos and Nevron reserves the right to assign ranks up to and including rank 3 for these people. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub86.ezboard.com/ukyrakasa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kyrakasa</A> at: 1/18/02 3:00:20 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub86.ezboard.com/fbringersofretributionfrm16.showPrevMessage?topicID=5.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub86.ezboard.com/fbringersofretributionfrm16.showNextMessage?topicID=5.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub86.ezboard.com/fbringersofretributionfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/slate/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub86.ezboard.com/fbringersofretributionfrm16.threadControl?topicID=5.topic><img src=http://www.tsa.nu/images/pix.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub86.ezboard.com/fbringersofretributionfrm16.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=5.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub86.ezboard.com/fbringersofretributionfrm16.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=5.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><for